---
// src/pages/about.astro
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout 
  title="About MoneyInFuture - Financial Calculators for Indian Investors"
  description="Learn about MoneyInFuture — free, privacy-first, offline-capable financial calculators built for Indian retail investors. No tracking, no cookies, no servers."
>
  <div class="calculator-header">
    <h1>About MoneyInFuture</h1>
    <p class="calculator-description">Fast, accurate, and privacy-first financial calculators for Indian retail investors.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="seo-content" style="max-width: 760px;">
    <h2>What is MoneyInFuture?</h2>
    <p>MoneyInFuture (Money In Future) is a free, open-access collection of personal finance calculators designed specifically for
      Indian investors. We cover SIP, SWP, EMI, CAGR, XIRR, FIRE, retirement planning, and more — all running
      entirely inside your browser.</p>

    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Our Privacy Commitment</h2>
    <p>Every calculation happens locally on your device. We do not collect, transmit, or store any of your
      financial data. There are no analytics trackers, cookies, or backend servers involved in running these
      calculators. Your financial information stays completely private.</p>

    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Technology</h2>
    <p>MoneyInFuture is built with vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript — no heavy frameworks, no npm bundles. This
      keeps the site fast, lightweight, and functional even on slow connections. The site is designed to work
      offline once loaded.</p>

    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Calculator Accuracy</h2>
    <p>All financial formulas are based on standard Indian investment conventions (CAGR-equivalent monthly
      compounding, annuity-due SIP timing, standard EMI formula). Calculations include clear assumptions. Where
      approximations are used (e.g., yearly compounding of monthly SIPs), this is documented in the calculator's
      assumptions section.</p>

    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Disclaimer</h2>
    <p>MoneyInFuture is an educational tool. Nothing on this site constitutes financial, tax, or investment
      advice. Please consult a qualified financial advisor before making investment decisions. See our full <a
        href="/disclaimer.html">Disclaimer</a>.</p>

    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Contact</h2>
    <p>Have a bug report, suggestion, or calculator request? <a href="/contact.html">Contact us here</a>.</p>
  </section>
</Layout>
